verses.text:
The kings of the nations on earth prepare to revolt;
\q2 the rulers plot together to fight against Yahweh and against his Anointed One.
\q1

But the one who sits on his throne in heaven laughs at them;
\q2 the Lord ridicules those rulers.
\q1

You have caused me to be very happy;
\q2 I am happier than people who have harvested a great amount of grain and grapes.
\q1

You are not a god who is pleased with wicked people;
\q2 you will never welcome those who do what is evil.
\q1

But cause that all those who go to you to be protected will rejoice;
\q2 cause them to sing joyfully to you forever.
\q1 Protect those who love you;
\q2 they are truly happy because of what you do for them.
\q1

Yahweh, do not correct me when you are angry with me;
\q2 do not punish me when you are upset.
\q1

God, you protect me as a shield protects soldiers;
\q2 you rescue all those who are righteous in their inner being.
\q1

You are preparing your weapons to kill those whom you strike;
\q2 the arrows that you will shoot have flaming tips.
\q1

You have taught little children and infants to praise you;
\q2 they cause your enemies and those who try to get revenge on you to be silent.
\q1

You made the angels in heaven to be only a little more important than we are;
\q2 you caused us to be like kings!
\q1

You put us in charge of everything that you made;
\q2 you gave us authority over all things—
\q1

He will judge all the people in the world justly;
\q2 he will be fair when he judges the people of every nation.
\q1

Yahweh will be a refuge for those who are oppressed;
\q2 he will be like a shelter for them when they have trouble.
\q1

Wicked people will all die and be buried in their graves;
\q2 their spirits will go to be with all those who have forgotten about you.
\q1

But I trust that you will faithfully love me;
\q2 I will rejoice when you rescue me.
\q1

I said to Yahweh, "You are my Lord;
\q all the good things that I have come from you."
\q1

People who try to be holy who live in this land are wonderful;
\q I delight to be with them.
\q1

I will praise Yahweh, the one who teaches me;
\q even at night he tells my heart what is right for me to do.
\q1

I have not acted like those who do not honor you;
\q2 I have always acted in the power of what you have instructed me;
\q1 I have not acted like those who do not know your law.
\q1

O God, I am praying to you because you answer me;
\q2 please listen to what I am saying.
\q1

Protect me as carefully as people protect their own eyes;
\q2 protect me like birds protect their babies under their wings.
\q1

When people look at everything that God has placed in the skies, they can see that he is very great;
\q2 they can see the great things that he has created.
\q1

But here is no one who can know all his errors;
\q2 so Yahweh, forgive me for these things which I do that I do not realize are wrong.
\q1

You will remove their children from this earth;
\q2 their descendants will all disappear.
\q1

They are like roaring lions that are attacking the animals that they want to eat;
\q2 they rush toward me to kill me;
\q1 they are like lions that have their mouths open, ready to chew their victims to pieces.
\q1

The earth and everything in it belongs to Yahweh;
\q2 all the people in the world belong to him, too;
\q1

Do you know who the glorious king is?
\q2 It is Yahweh, commander of the angel armies;
\q2 he is our glorious king!

Yahweh, do not forget how you have acted mercifully to me and have faithfully loved me because of your covenant with me;
\q2 that is the way that you have acted toward me from long ago.
\q1

I have many troubles that make me afraid;
\q2 rescue me from them.
\q1

Note that I have many enemies;
\q2 you see that they hate me very much.
\q1

Protect me and rescue me from them;
\q2 do not allow them to defeat me
\q2 with the result that I would be ashamed;
\q1 I have gone to you to get refuge.
\q1

Yahweh, examine what I have done and test me;
\q2 thoroughly evaluate what I think in my inner being.
\q1

I never forget that you are true to your covenant and faithfully love me;
\q2 I conduct my life according to your faithfulness.
\q1

Do not get rid of me like you get rid of sinners;
\q2 do not cause me to die like you cause those who murder people to die,
\q1

Punish those people in the way that they deserve for what they have done;
\q2 punish them for their evil deeds.
\q1

Yahweh causes us to be strong and protects us;
\q2 he saves me, the one he appointed to be king.
\q1

Yahweh, save your people;
\q2 bless those who belong to you.
\q1 Take care of them like a shepherd takes care of his sheep;
\q2 take care of them forever.

He causes earthquakes to shake the region of Lebanon as a young cow jumps;
\q2 he causes Mount Hermon to shake as a young bull jumps.
\q1

His voice causes the desert to shake;
\q2 he shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
\q1

Yahweh rules over the flood that covered the earth;
\q2 he is our king who will rule forever.
\q1

Yes, you are like my huge rock and my fort;
\q2 guide me and lead me because I worship you.
\q1

I have become very weak because I am so miserable;
\q2 my life is getting shorter.
\q1 I have become weak because of all my troubles;
\q2 even my bones are becoming weaker.
\q1

Yahweh always does what he says that he will do;
\q2 we can trust that everything that he does is right.
\q1

Everyone on the earth should honor Yahweh;
\q2 everyone on the earth should honor him.
\q1

Yahweh blesses our nation, we who worship him;
\q2 How fortunate are we, the nation that belongs to him forever!
\q1

We trust Yahweh to help us;
\q2 he protects us as a shield protects a soldier.
\q1

We rejoice because of what he has done for us;
\q2 we trust in him because he is holy.
\q1

I will always thank Yahweh;
\q2 I will constantly praise him.
\q1

I prayed to Yahweh, and he answered my prayer;
\q2 he rescued me from all those who caused me to be afraid.
\q1

Those who trust that he will help them will be joyful;
\q2 they will never have to look down in disgrace.
\q1

Yahweh carefully watches over those who act righteously;
\q2 he always responds to them when they call to him for help.
\q1

Yahweh hears righteous people when they call out to him;
\q2 he rescues them from all their troubles.
\q1

Then I will rejoice in what you, Yahweh, have done for me;
\q2 I will be glad that you have rescued me.
\q1

They do not speak peacefully to people;
\q2 instead, they look for ways to tell lies about people in our land who do no harm to anyone.
\q1

Yahweh, your faithful love for us reaches as high as the heavens;
\q2 your faithfulness in doing what you have promised extends up to the clouds.
\q1

You provide for us plenty of food from the abundant supply that you have;
\q2 your great gifts flow to us like a river.
\q1

Wicked people plan to harm righteous people;
\q2 they snarl at them like wild animals.
\q1

Day by day Yahweh protects those who have not done any evil things;
\q2 the things that Yahweh gives them will last forever.
\q1

The wicked people borrow money, but they are not able to repay it;
\q2 righteous people, in contrast, have enough money to give generously to others.
\q1

Yahweh protects those who do what is pleasing to him,
\q2 and he will enable them to walk confidently wherever they go;
\q1

Notice the people who have not done evil things, those who act righteously;
\q2 their descendants will have peace in their inner beings.
\q1

Yahweh rescues righteous people;
\q2 in times of trouble he protects them.
\q1

Yahweh helps them and saves them;
\q2 he rescues them from being attacked by wicked people
\q2 because they go to him to be protected.

Now it is as though you have shot your arrows at me and wounded me;
\q2 it is as though you have struck me and knocked me down.
\q1

Sometimes I am bent over, and sometimes I lie prostrate;
\q2 I mourn all day.
\q1

Yahweh, you know that I desire you to heal me;
\q2 you hear me while I am groaning.
\q1

My friends and neighbors stay away from me because of my sores;
\q2 even my own family stays far from me.
\q1

Those who want to kill me set traps to catch me;
\q2 those who want to harm me discuss the ways that they can get rid of me;
\q2 they plot against me all day.
\b
\q1

I confess the wrong things that I have done;
\q2 I am very sorry for the sins that I have committed.
\q1

My enemies are healthy and strong;
\q2 there are many people who hate me for no reason.
\q1

So I was completely silent, and I did not even talk about things that were good;
\q2 but it was useless because I began to suffer even more.
\q1

How fortunate are those who provide for the poor;
\q2 Yahweh will rescue those people when they have troubles.
\q1

When I was sick, I said, "Yahweh, act mercifully toward me and heal me;
\q2 I know that I am sick because I have sinned against you."
\q1

My enemies say cruel things about me;
\q2 they say, "How soon will he die, and then everyone will forget about him?"
\q1

They say, "He will soon die because of his being sick;
\q2 he will never get up from his bed before he dies."
\q1

Every day and every night I weep;
\q2 the only thing I have to drink is my tears;
\q1 and while I do that, my enemies are always asking me,
\q2 "Why does your God not help you?"
\q1

You are my king and my God;
\q2 Make us, your people, able to defeat our enemies.
\q1

No, it is you who have rescued us from our enemies;
\q2 it is you who have caused those who hate us to become ashamed because they were defeated.
\q1

But now you have rejected us and caused us to be disgraced;
\q2 when our armies march out to fight a battle, you no longer go with them.
\q1

You have allowed us to become like sheep that were ready to be slaughtered;
\q2 you scattered us far away among other nations.
\q

People who live in nations near us make fun of us;
\q2 they laugh at us and deride us.
\q1

All day I am disgraced;
\q2 from seeing my face, people know that I am ashamed.
\q

We are in complete panic;
\q2 we cannot do anything; we are as good as dead.
\q1

God is the one who protects us and causes us to be strong;
\q2 he is always ready to help us when we have troubles.
\q1

God is in this city, and it will never be destroyed;
\q2 he will come to help the people in that city at dawn every day.
\q1

Sometimes the people of many nations are terrified;
\q2 kingdoms are overthrown;
\q1 God speaks loudly like thunder,
\q2 and the earth melts.
\b
\q1

He stops wars all over the world;
\q2 he breaks bows and arrows;
\q2 he destroys spears;
\q2 he burns up shields.
\q1

Yahweh, who is much greater than any other god, is awesome;
\q2 he is a king who rules over all the world!
\q1

God is the one who rules over everything in the world;
\q2 sing a psalm to him!
\q1

The rulers of those people groups gather in front of God's people, the people descended from Abraham.
\q1 God has more power than the weapons of all the kings on the earth;
\q2 he is great, and all people everywhere will honor him.

but when they saw it, they were amazed;
\q2 they became terrified, and ran away.
\q1

You Israelite people should walk around Mount Zion 
\q2 and count the towers there;
\q1

So do not be dismayed when someone becomes rich
\q2 and the houses where they live become more and more luxurious;
\q1

for when he dies, he will take nothing with him;
\q2 his wealth will not go with him.
\q1

I say that because I know the ways that I have disobeyed you;
\q2 I cannot forget them.
\q1

I have been a sinner since the day that I was born;
\q2 truly, I have been like that since my mother conceived me.
\q1

Forgive the guilt of my sins, and after that happens, I will be completely acceptable to you;
\q2 if you forgive me, then I will be absolutely right with you.
\q1

If you do that, I will teach other sinners what you want them to do;
\q2 they will repent and obey you.
\q1

O God, be good to the people who live in Jerusalem;
\q2 make them able to rebuild the city walls.
\q1

"Look what happened to the man who would not ask God to protect him;
\q2 he trusted that his great wealth would save him;
\q2 he grew more powerful by wickedly hurting other people."
\b
\q1

But God is the one who helps me;
\q2 Yahweh defends me from my enemies.
\q1

Yahweh, I will gladly give an offering to you because I want to,
\q2 and I will thank you, for you are good to me;
\q1

My enemies terrify me;
\q2 wicked people oppress me.
\q2 They cause me to have great troubles;
\q2 they are angry with me, and they hate me.
\b
\q1

I am very fearful and I tremble;
\q2 I am completely terrified.
\q1

All day long my enemies claim that I said things that I did not say;
\q2 they are always thinking of ways to harm me.
\q1

So, God, punish them for the wicked things that they are doing;
\q2 show that you are angry by defeating those people!
\q1

When I call out to you, my God, my enemies will be defeated;
\q2 I know that will happen because you are fighting for me.
\q1

I praise you that you do what you have promised;
\q2 Yahweh, I will always praise you for that.
\q2

I will bring to you the offering that I promised;
\q1 I will bring an offering to you to thank you
\q1

Sometimes I am surrounded by my enemies, who are as ready to kill me as lions are to kill people;
\q2 they are like lions that chew to bits the animals that they kill.
\q1 But my enemies are human, and they have spears and arrows, not teeth;
\q2 they say false things about me.
\b
\q1

Lord, I will thank you among all the people;
\q1 and I will sing songs of praise about you to many people groups.
\q2

When you rulers speak, you never say what is right;
\q2 you people never justly decide disputes.
\q1

People who do what is right will rejoice when they see God punish the wicked people;
\q2 they will wash their feet in the blood of wicked people.
\q1

God, I have confidence in you because you are very strong;
\q2 you are my refuge.
\q1

God, you are the one who enables me to be strong;
\q2 you are my refuge;
\q2 you faithfully love me, just as you have promised in your covenant.

The region of Gilead is mine;
\q1 the people of the tribe of Manasseh are mine;
\q1 the tribe of Ephraim is like my helmet;
\q1 and the tribe of Judah is like the scepter with which I rule.
\q1

The region of Moab is like my washbasin;
\q2 I throw my sandal into the region of Edom to show that it belongs to me;
\q2 I shout triumphantly because I have defeated the people of all the region of Philistia.
\b
\q1

So, God, it seems that you have truly abandoned us;
\q2 it seems that you do not go with us when our armies march out to fight our enemies.
\q1

God is the only one who gives me peace in my inner being;
\q2 he is the one whom I confidently expect to help me.
\q1

Only he is like a huge rock on which I can be safe;
\q2 he is like a shelter; my enemies can never reach me there.
\q1

I will praise you all the time that I live;
\q2 I will lift up my hands to you while I pray.
\q1

But those who are trying to kill me
\q2 will die and descend into the place of the dead;
\q1

But I, the king of Israel, will rejoice in what God has done;
\q2 and all those who ask God to confirm their word will praise him,
\q2 but he will not allow liars to say anything.

The hostile things they say are like sharp swords;
\q2 their cruel words are like arrows.
\q1

Righteous people should rejoice because of what Yahweh has done;
\q2 they should go to him to find refuge;
\q1 and all those who honor him will praise him.

God, when we pray to you, you answer us and save us by doing awesome deeds;
\q2 you are the one who rescues us;
\q1 people who live in very remote places on the earth, on the other side of the oceans, trust in you.
\q1

Because you bless the soil, there are very good crops at harvest season;
\q2 wherever you have gone, good crops are very abundant.
\q1

The meadows are covered with sheep and goats,
\q2 and the valleys are full of grain;
\q2 it is as though they also sing and shout joyfully.

I will bring to your temple offerings that are to be completely burned on the altar;
\q2 I will offer to you what I promised.
\q1

When I was experiencing much trouble, I said that I would bring offerings to you if you rescued me;
\q2 and you did rescue me, so I will bring to you what I promised.
\q1

I praise God
\q2 because he has not ignored my prayers;
\q2 he continues to love me as he promised in his covenant to do.

God, act mercifully toward us and bless us;
\q1 act kindly toward us.
\q2

God, I desire that all people groups may praise you;
\q1 I want them all to praise you!
\q1

Good crops have grown on our land;
\q1 God, our God, has blessed us.
\q1

But may the righteous people be joyful;
\q2 may they rejoice when they are in God's presence;
\q2 may they be happy and very joyful.
\b
\q1

Sing to God; sing to praise him;
\q1 sing a song for him who rides in the desert plains;
\q1 his name is Yahweh; be glad when you are in his presence.
\q1

Praise the Lord, who helps us carry our heavy loads every day;
\q1 he is the one who saves us.
\q1

They are all singing, "You Israelite people, praise God when you gather together;
\q2 praise Yahweh, all you who are descendants of Jacob!"
\q1

Show us that you are strong, there where you are in your temple in Jerusalem;
\q2 kings bring gifts to you there.
\q1

Even my own older brothers act as if they do not know me;
\q2 they treat me like a foreigner.
\q1

Do not allow the floods to swirl around me;
\q2 do not allow the deep mud to swallow me;
\q2 keep me from sinking into the pit of death.
\q1

I hope their own food will kill them;
\q2 I hope that this will happen when they think that they are completely safe.
\q1

Cause their towns to become abandoned;
\q2 may there be no one to live in their tents.
\q1

Yahweh, I have come to you to be safe;
\q2 never allow me to become ashamed.
\q1

Because you always do what is right, help me and rescue me;
\q2 listen to me, and save me!
\q1

Yahweh, my Lord, you are the one whom I confidently expect to help me;
\q2 I have trusted in you ever since I was young.
\q1

Now when I have become an old man, do not reject me;
\q2 do not abandon me now when I am not strong anymore.
\q1

My enemies say that they want to kill me;
\q2 they talk together and plan how they can do that.
\q1

God, do not stay far away from me;
\q2 hurry to help me!
\q1

Yahweh, my Lord, I will praise you for your mighty deeds;
\q2 I will proclaim that only you always act justly.
\q1

God, you do many righteous deeds;
\q2 it is as though they extend up to the sky.
\q1 You have done great things;
\q2 there is no one like you.
\q1

He pities those who are weak and needy;
\q2 he saves the people's lives.
\q1

Praise Yahweh, the God whom we Israelites worship;
\q2 he is the only one who does wonderful things.
\q1

As for me, I almost stopped trusting in God;
\q1 I was almost guilty of committing a great sin against him
\q1

Those people do not suffer from sickness;
\q2 they are always strong and healthy.
\q1

They do not have the troubles that other people have;
\q2 they do not have problems as others do.
\q1

They scoff at other people, and they talk about doing evil things to them;
\q1 they are proud while they plan to oppress others.
\q1

They will be destroyed instantly;
\q2 they will die in terrible ways.
\q

You are in heaven, and I belong to you;
\q1 there is nothing on this earth that I desire more than that.
\q1

Those who remain far from you will be destroyed;
\q1 you will get rid of those who abandon you.
\q1

Your enemies shouted triumphantly in this sacred place;
\q1 they erected their banners to show they had defeated us.
\q1

Then they burned your temple to the ground;
\q2 they caused that place where you were worshiped to be unfit for people to worship in.
\q1

By your power you caused the sea to divide;
\q2 it was as though you had smashed the heads of the rulers of Egypt who were like huge sea dragons.
\q1

Do not abandon your helpless people into the hands of their cruel enemies;
\q1 do not forget your suffering people.
\q1

Continue thinking about the covenant that you made with us;
\q2 remember that there are violent people in every dark place on the earth.
\q1

God is the one who judges people;
\q2 he shames and punishes some, and he honors others.
\q1

It is as though Yahweh held a cup in his hand;
\q2 it is filled with wine that has spices mixed in it to cause those who drink it to become more drunk;
\q1 and when Yahweh pours it out, he will force all the wicked people to drink it;
\q2 they will drink every drop of it; yes, he will punish them fully.
\b
\q1

But as for me, I will never stop saying what the God whom Jacob worshiped has done;
\q1 I will never stop singing to praise him.
\q1

God has made the people in Judah to know him;
\q1 the Israelite people honor him.
\q1

In Jerusalem is where he resides;
\q2 he lives on Mount Zion.
\q1

So give to Yahweh the offerings that you promised to give to him;
\q2 all the people of nearby people groups should also bring gifts to him, the one who is awesome.
\q1

I will cry out to God;
\q1 I will cry aloud to him, and he will listen to me.
\q1

When I thought about God, I despaired;
\q1 when I meditated about him, I grew discouraged.
\q1

All during the night he prevented me from sleeping;
\q2 I was so worried that I did not know what to say.
\q1

I thought about days that had passed;
\q2 I remembered what had happened in previous years.
\q1

I spent all the night thinking about things;
\q2 I meditated, and this is what I asked myself:
\q1

But then, Yahweh, I recall your great deeds;
\q2 I remember the wonderful things that you did in the past.
\q2

God, everything that you do is amazing;
\q2 there is certainly no god who is great like you are!
\q1

You are God, the one who performs miracles;
\q2 you showed to the people of many people groups that you are powerful.
\q1

My friends, listen to what I am going to teach you;
\q2 pay careful attention to what I will say.
\q1

They did not do what they had agreed with God that they would do;
\q2 they refused to obey his laws.
\q1

They forgot what he had done;
\q2 they forgot about the miracles that they had seen him perform.
\q1

But our ancestors continued to sin against God;
\q1 in the wilderness they rebelled against the one who is greater than any other god.
\q1

So he made them terrified all their lives;
\q2 he made them die young.
\q1

But they tried to deceive God by what they said;
\q2 their words were all lies.
\q1

They were not loyal to him;
\q2 they ignored the covenant that he had made with them.
\q1

Instead, as their ancestors did, they rebelled against God and were not loyal to him;
\q2 they were as unreliable as a bow that breaks when you try to shoot with it.
\q1

Later, it was as though the Lord awoke from sleeping;
\q1 he was like a strong man who became angry because he drank a lot of wine.
\q1

But he did not set up his tent where the people of the tribe of Ephraim lived;
\q2 he did not choose their area to do that.
\q1

Instead he chose the area where the tribe of Judah lived;
\q2 he chose Mount Zion, which he loves.
\q1

Our enemies have torn down and burned everything in our land;
\q1 look at them angrily and get rid of them!
\q1

Sing songs to praise God, who enables us to be strong when we fight our enemies;
\q1 shout joyfully to God, whom we descendants of Jacob worship!
\q1

Do that because that is a decree for us Israelite people;
\q2 it is a command that God made for the descendants of Jacob.
\q2

You must not have any idols of other gods among you;
\q2 you must never bow to worship any of them!
\q1

I am Yahweh, your God;
\q2 It was not any of those gods who brought you out of Egypt;
\q1 I am the one who did it!
\q2 So request what you want me to do for you, and I will do it.
\b
\q1

But my people would not listen to me;
\q2 they would not obey me.
\q1

If they did that, I would quickly defeat their enemies;
\q2 I would strike dead those who are oppressing them.
\q1

"You must stop judging people unfairly;
\q1 you must no longer make decisions that favor wicked people!
\q1

You must defend people who are poor and orphans;
\q2 you must act fairly toward those who are needy and those who have no one to help them.
\q1

because your enemies are rioting against you;
\q2 those who hate you are rebelling against you!
\q1

They are secretly planning to do things to harm us, your people;
\q2 they are conspiring together against the people whom you protect.
\q1

Do to them things like you did to kings Oreb and Zeeb;
\q2 defeat their leaders like you defeated Zebah and Zalmunna,
\q2

Yahweh, commander of the angel armies, listen to my prayer;
\q1 God, whom we descendants of Jacob worship, hear what I am saying!
\q1

Yahweh, you have acted kindly toward us people who live in this land;
\q1 you have enabled us Israelite people to become prosperous again.
\q1

You forgave us, your people, for the sins that we had committed;
\q2 you pardoned us for all our sins.
\q1

Prevent me from dying now because I am loyal to you;
\q2 save me because I serve you and I trust in you, my God.
\q1

Lord, you are good to us, and you forgive us;
\q1 you faithfully love very much all those who pray to you.
\q1

Yahweh, listen to my prayer;
\q2 hear me when I cry out to you to help me.
\q1

But God, proud men are trying to attack me;
\q2 a gang of cruel men are wanting to kill me;
\q2 they are men who do not have any respect for you.
